        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1543583988" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1553960718172815238">I confess that I&apos;m rating the movie (1968) along with this play. I couldn&apos;t divorce the two in my mind when reading the play. The movie follows the play entirely with the movie adding the settings that help to comprehend the play. The movie is among my favorites of all time specifically because of the word play and the dialogue. And with Katherine Hepburn as Eleanor or Aquitaine...well it simply doesn&apos;t get any better. This play is a brilliant representation of family dynamics and politics on st</span>
  <span id="freeText1553960718172815238" style="display:none">I confess that I'm rating the movie (1968) along with this play. I couldn't divorce the two in my mind when reading the play. The movie follows the play entirely with the movie adding the settings that help to comprehend the play. The movie is among my favorites of all time specifically because of the word play and the dialogue. And with Katherine Hepburn as Eleanor or Aquitaine...well it simply doesn't get any better. This play is a brilliant representation of family dynamics and politics on steroids. Genius work!!<br /><br /><i>Almost 4.5 Stars</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="1553960718172815238" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

